  "authorized_conclusions": [
    "A Gaussian distribution of local gaps convolved with a square-root intrinsic edge reproduces the Herrmann approximately-s-over-two tail scale over the source-stated 1-100 cm^-1 range.",
    "The convolved spectrum is not exactly exponential; fitted tail energy depends on the absorption window.",
    "High log-linear R-squared does not identify the latent gap width or intrinsic-edge exponent.",
    "An observed Urbach-like energy cannot be converted to sigma_G without an explicit intrinsic edge, normalization, and fit window."
